## JavaScript Function Basics

```javascript
// Function declaration
function greet(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

// Function usage
const message = greet('World');
console.log(message);
```

### Key Concepts
* Function Definition
* Function Invocation

## Conditional Statements in JavaScript

```javascript
// Example of a conditional statement
if (temperature > 30) {
    console.log('It is a hot day!');
} else {
    console.log('Temperature is moderate.');
}
```

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Check Temperature] --> B{Is temp > 30?}
    B -- Yes --> C[Log 'Hot day']
    B -- No --> D[Log 'Moderate temp']
```

## Loops in JavaScript

```javascript
// Using a for loop
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    console.log('Iteration:', i);
}
```

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start Loop] --> B{Condition True?}
    B -- Yes --> C[Execute Loop Body]
    C --> D[Increment]
    D --> B
    B -- No --> E[End Loop]
```

## Error Handling in JavaScript

```javascript
try {
    // Code that may throw an error
    riskyFunction();
} catch (error) {
    console.error('An error occurred:', error);
}
```

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant App
    User->>App: Execute risky function
    App->>App: Try block execution
    App-->>User: Handle error if occurs
```

